WEBVTT

00:00.130 --> 00:05.916
We've been talking a lot this weekend about the enjoyment of Jesus or enjoying Jesus.

00:06.016 --> 00:20.469
And I made the case on Friday that becoming a Christian or being born again or coming to saving faith is the awakening of the enjoyment of Jesus.

00:21.611 --> 00:29.458
And I pointed out that that is an unsettling fact for many because if you

00:31.586 --> 00:38.074
make them so closely related as to be necessarily in each other.

00:38.114 --> 00:41.098
If you're saved, you enjoy Jesus.

00:42.499 --> 00:45.904
To believe is to enjoy Jesus.

00:47.946 --> 00:55.836
It makes our faith feel fragile because our joy goes so up and down.

00:58.619 --> 01:01.042
So are you sure you want to do that, Piper?

01:01.890 --> 01:10.462
make them so closely connected, doesn't that tend to undermine people's assurance?

01:13.326 --> 01:21.697
And so let me head off at the past a misunderstanding, namely that Christian salvation is fragile.

01:22.459 --> 01:22.939
It's not.

01:23.941 --> 01:26.344
It's anything but fragile.

01:27.706 --> 01:30.770
Those whom he predestined, he called.

01:31.330 --> 01:34.174
And those of me called, he justified.

01:34.775 --> 01:38.101
And those of me justified, he glorified.

01:40.685 --> 01:42.227
That's as solid as it can get.

01:43.890 --> 01:47.756
From eternity to eternity, sure.

01:48.797 --> 01:51.922
An unbreakable chain from predestination

01:52.162 --> 02:02.517
to glorification and all the pieces in between of calling and justification and everything else that belongs to salvation is secure.

02:04.220 --> 02:09.127
If you're predestined, if you're called, if you're justified, you're going to make it.

02:10.169 --> 02:14.936
So I have no wobbly view of Christian salvation.

02:15.536 --> 02:22.066
I don't think it can be lost and therefore when I make it integral,

02:22.818 --> 02:30.768
to enjoying Jesus, I don't treat it as wobbly or uncertain.

02:32.450 --> 02:48.350
You don't solve the problem of the ups and downs of enjoying Jesus as if faith didn't have its ups and downs.

02:50.113 --> 02:51.314
It's like, oh,

02:51.810 --> 02:55.054
Joy is in emotion and therefore fragile.

02:55.454 --> 02:59.118
Faith is something that doesn't go up and down.

02:59.259 --> 02:59.979
That's not true.

03:01.741 --> 03:03.984
Jesus referred to little faith.

03:05.446 --> 03:07.728
Big, all your faith is great.

03:09.190 --> 03:12.414
Paul spoke of growing faith.

03:14.837 --> 03:19.602
So faith is not something that also doesn't.

03:20.642 --> 03:23.425
go up and down in our lives.

03:25.007 --> 03:31.775
So if the ups and downs of joy in our life feel threatening, then so will the ups and downs of faith.

03:31.935 --> 03:33.857
That's not the way to solve the problem.

03:36.079 --> 03:43.648
So we're going to talk about the ups and downs, especially the down of enjoying Jesus.

03:43.708 --> 03:48.914
That's where we're going this morning.

03:51.170 --> 03:59.699
I don't know what group I asked, I can't remember, but I love to ask groups, I'll ask you, what makes you think that you will wake up a believer tomorrow morning?

04:00.720 --> 04:06.387
What makes you think that you'll wake up and be a Christian in the morning?

04:08.469 --> 04:10.691
And there's a wrong answer to that question.

04:11.572 --> 04:18.780
And the wrong answer would be something like, I know beyond the shadow of it out that I will use my free will to believe in Jesus tomorrow morning.

04:19.041 --> 04:20.402
Well, you know no such thing.

04:24.802 --> 04:25.663
Here's what you know.

04:25.683 --> 04:31.329
Now on to Him who is able to keep you from falling.

04:32.250 --> 04:44.824
And to present you blameless before the presence of His glory with rejoicing, to the only God I save you through Jesus Christ, our Lord be glory and authority and majesty and dominion forever.

04:44.884 --> 04:46.967
That's what you know.

04:46.987 --> 04:50.030
If you're a believer, He keeps His own.

04:51.212 --> 04:53.394
Those of me calls, He keeps.

04:53.538 --> 05:00.324
I will wake up a believer tomorrow morning because God has kept me or I won't be a believer tomorrow morning.

05:02.146 --> 05:04.008
We trust in God, not ourselves.

05:05.389 --> 05:15.499
So the security that we enjoy, the assurance that we have, that the ups and downs of our joy and the ups and downs of our faith don't destroy us.

05:15.539 --> 05:15.979
They won't.

05:16.520 --> 05:23.346
God has patterns built into the Bible to help us manage the downs.

05:23.810 --> 05:25.272
It's not hard to manage the ops.

05:26.693 --> 05:29.576
And that's what we're talking about this morning.

05:29.616 --> 05:37.585
There is a fight for faith and the fight for faith is a fight for joy.

05:38.346 --> 05:48.978
If I was right on Friday night that to have saving faith in Jesus is to be awakened to the enjoyment of Jesus.

05:49.314 --> 05:55.041
So when Paul speaks to Timothy and says, fight the good fight of faith.

05:55.882 --> 05:58.165
It's the same as saying fight for joy.

05:59.106 --> 06:05.814
I wrote a book called When I Don't Desire God and the subtitle is How to Fight for Joy.

06:07.095 --> 06:09.358
I'm old and Paul was old.

06:09.859 --> 06:13.823
He called himself an old man one time in the book of Philemon and he was in prison.

06:14.324 --> 06:16.427
Great place to end your life, by the way.

06:16.447 --> 06:19.250
It goes quicker that way probably.

06:22.178 --> 06:25.121
in case you're wondering what to do with your last 20 years.

06:28.865 --> 06:39.536
He was in prison and he wrote the last book of the New Testament that he wrote, 2 Timothy, and he said, I have fought the good fight.

06:40.137 --> 06:41.498
I have finished the course.

06:42.339 --> 06:48.786
I have kept the faith, which I take to mean old men fight to the end, and they better not stop.

06:50.338 --> 06:56.604
If you think that you can fight for 60 or 80 years and then stop for a year or two, you're crazy.

06:58.005 --> 07:01.488
The devil does not sleep.

07:01.509 --> 07:06.513
His fiery darts shoot at old people and young people.

07:06.533 --> 07:09.456
We fight to the end and God has taught us how to do it.

07:09.796 --> 07:10.857
And that's what we're talking about.

07:11.798 --> 07:20.146
How to fight your way through the slump when you wake up and there's almost no joy.

07:21.762 --> 07:25.067
in Jesus.

07:25.087 --> 07:30.797
So if you have a Bible, what you hope you do, at least on your phone, let's go to, oh, you just turned your phones off.

07:30.817 --> 07:34.302
How do you do?

07:34.322 --> 07:35.765
Got print Bibles around here.

07:35.785 --> 07:36.706
That's good.

07:37.427 --> 07:39.751
Let's go to the Bible.

07:41.053 --> 07:41.895
However you've got it.

07:42.776 --> 07:43.517
Psalm 40.

07:43.557 --> 07:48.946
And we're going to read verses one to three.

07:50.466 --> 08:07.666
which are a pattern of how David managed his loss of spiritual dynamic joy.

08:09.108 --> 08:09.829
What did he do?

08:11.351 --> 08:17.458
And I think as Christians on this side of the cross, we can

08:18.114 --> 08:20.477
embrace these verses as our own.

08:25.083 --> 08:47.794
Paul said in Galatians 4, when the fullness of time had come, God sent forth His Son, born of woman, born under the law, that He might redeem those who were under the law, in order that they might be adopted as sons.

08:48.770 --> 09:01.927
We know God today as our Father in a unique and special way unknown in the same detail in the Old Testament.

09:02.387 --> 09:04.770
They didn't know how this was going to work.

09:04.790 --> 09:17.106
They didn't know that blood was going to be shed by the incarnate God as the Messiah who would cover all the sins old and New Testament and who would bring the saints into a sweet intimate

09:17.634 --> 09:30.431
child-adopted relationship with the Father so that when we call upon God like this text does, we're calling now upon God as a father that we have because of adoption through the blood of Jesus.

09:30.811 --> 09:34.816
So I'm reading this text because I read my whole Bible.

09:34.856 --> 09:39.282
I understand it as a completed

09:39.522 --> 09:43.966
hold the Old Testament preparing and the New Testament fulfilling.

09:44.367 --> 09:53.235
And I think you then did stand back and see all the promises of God bought by Jesus Christ and you can make the Old Testament your book.

09:53.755 --> 10:00.642
And so I'm reading this as my Christian book here, these three verses in Psalm 40.

10:01.803 --> 10:04.025
I think Jesus bought this text for you.

10:05.526 --> 10:07.008
If you are in Him, it's yours.

10:08.309 --> 10:09.490
To the choir master.

10:10.306 --> 10:15.913
a psalm of David, I waited patiently for the Lord.

10:17.655 --> 10:19.838
He inclined to me and heard my cry.

10:21.299 --> 10:32.533
He drew me up from the pit of destruction out of the myry bog and set my feet upon a rock, making my steps secure.

10:33.354 --> 10:40.082
He put a new song in my mouth, a song of praise to our God, many

10:40.386 --> 10:46.034
will see and fear and put their trust in the Lord.

10:47.435 --> 10:51.381
Now I think that's a pattern of life that we live.

10:52.702 --> 10:57.649
I'm tempted to say every day, at least regularly.

10:59.031 --> 11:07.442
So I'm, I'm asking, is it, is it normal to have Christian seasons in the pit with the king?

11:09.122 --> 11:10.884
And what do you do when you go there?

11:11.324 --> 11:13.286
That's what this message is about.

11:13.327 --> 11:16.069
And that's what this text, I think, answers.

11:16.790 --> 11:18.172
I see six stages.

11:18.732 --> 11:22.677
If I were teaching a class instead of preaching a sermon, I would have you find the stages.

11:24.519 --> 11:28.283
First, David is in a muddy pit, verse two.

11:29.184 --> 11:33.348
Calls it a pit of destruction, mighty bog in the ESV.

11:33.368 --> 11:37.893
Second, he cries out to God from this pit for help.

11:38.213 --> 11:38.994
Verse one,

11:39.298 --> 11:40.179
He heard my cry.

11:41.381 --> 11:43.284
Three, he waits.

11:43.825 --> 11:44.446
How long?

11:44.466 --> 11:45.247
I don't know how long.

11:45.328 --> 11:46.710
I'm glad he didn't tell me how long.

11:47.351 --> 11:49.815
He waits for the Lord.

11:50.416 --> 11:53.961
Verse one, I waited patiently for the Lord.

11:54.823 --> 11:59.891
Four, God draws him up out of the pit into safety.

11:59.991 --> 12:02.936
Verse two, he drew me up out of the pit.

12:03.677 --> 12:06.962
Five, God gives David a new song.

12:07.746 --> 12:11.692
to sing, probably the one we're reading, Psalm 40.

12:12.453 --> 12:14.997
Verse three, he put a new song in my mouth.

12:16.058 --> 12:29.638
And finally verse, or step six, many see, many others see what happened to David and they fear and they put their trust in the Lord.

12:29.839 --> 12:32.082
Verse three, many will see in fear.

12:32.194 --> 12:33.496
and put their trust in the Lord.

12:33.516 --> 12:46.673
So I'll give them names and then we'll take them one at a time and walk you through them because this is where we, I want you to simply take away from this message, okay, that's what I'll do.

12:47.054 --> 12:47.675
That's what I'll do.

12:48.896 --> 12:55.145
When my spirits are low and when my joy seems to vanish, this is what I'm going to do.

12:55.625 --> 12:59.230
So I want you to just get a real clear sense of what these six stages are.

12:59.270 --> 13:02.034
The king's pit.

13:02.754 --> 13:13.431
The kings cry, the kings patience, the kings rescue, the kings song, and the kings influence.

13:14.513 --> 13:17.437
And I think you can just put your name on it if you're a Christian.

13:17.658 --> 13:22.606
You just put your name on it and say that was the saints experience in the Old Testament.

13:23.146 --> 13:25.029
I'm in the Messiah, Jesus Christ.

13:25.650 --> 13:28.054
That can be my experience today.

13:28.255 --> 13:30.418
So let's take them one at a time first.

13:31.810 --> 13:32.531
He's in the pits.

13:34.253 --> 13:35.254
What was that?

13:35.334 --> 13:35.875
What is that?

13:36.396 --> 13:37.217
There's a little pit.

13:37.257 --> 13:39.119
Is that a picture of something?

13:40.641 --> 13:42.823
In ESV, it's the pit of destruction.

13:43.324 --> 13:45.727
In the King James, it's a horrible pit.

13:46.107 --> 13:47.950
In the RSV, it's a desolate pit.

13:48.430 --> 13:51.434
In the NIV, it's a slimy pit.

13:52.375 --> 13:55.739
You look up the word and get the most root definition.

13:56.060 --> 14:01.266
It has to do with roaring and a tumal, which is an odd picture for a pit.

14:02.082 --> 14:05.107
You don't think of, I'm in a pit and there's a storm in the pit.

14:05.307 --> 14:06.008
That's odd.

14:06.589 --> 14:08.492
These are not photographs, right?

14:08.833 --> 14:16.766
These are word pictures chosen to help us feel the soul condition that he was in.

14:16.786 --> 14:19.270
And then you got mud, mire.

14:20.632 --> 14:21.894
And they don't seem to go together.

14:21.914 --> 14:29.266
This roaring pit, like a well, like 30, 40 feet down,

14:29.826 --> 14:36.033
And you're down there, and there's a storm down there, and there's mud down there.

14:36.053 --> 14:37.695
It's Meyer.

14:37.715 --> 14:49.049
It reminded me of, because I'm reading, I suppose, through Jeremiah right now in my devotions, what happened to Jeremiah when Zedekiah got so ticked at this prophet.

14:49.690 --> 14:51.532
Here's what it says in Jeremiah 38.6.

14:51.752 --> 14:59.762
So they took Jeremiah and cast him into the cistern of Malchia, the king's son,

15:00.386 --> 15:03.729
which was in the court of the guard letting Jeremiah down with ropes.

15:03.930 --> 15:06.112
That was nice at least.

15:06.592 --> 15:14.120
And there was no water in the cistern, but only Meyer and Jeremiah sank in the Meyer.

15:15.181 --> 15:15.882
That's scary.

15:17.784 --> 15:19.045
Quicksand is scary.

15:19.165 --> 15:21.067
I don't like movies that have quicksand.

15:21.808 --> 15:22.649
There's horrible.

15:22.669 --> 15:23.590
I mean nightmares.

15:24.691 --> 15:27.954
They can't stand the thought of thinking in Quicksand.

15:28.162 --> 15:31.587
And that seems to be something of the picture here.

15:31.647 --> 15:33.931
It's helplessness, it's desperation.

15:35.092 --> 15:37.075
Air starts to become precious to you.

15:37.095 --> 15:38.778
Am I ever going to get out of here?

15:39.138 --> 15:45.327
That's a description of the emotion of your life at times, maybe today.

15:46.509 --> 15:47.410
Eventually it will be.

15:51.256 --> 15:57.906
Helpless, desperate, maybe hopeless, because you just can't feel anything anymore.

15:59.298 --> 16:10.132
A breaking point for an overworked businessman, exasperation to the limit of a mom with three kids that are all crying and they're little and she's just at her wits end.

16:10.172 --> 16:13.016
Too many classes for a student.

16:13.096 --> 16:14.097
I can't do this, Dad.

16:14.137 --> 16:16.760
I can't do this, this college thing.

16:16.780 --> 16:19.904
A powerful enemy coming against you.

16:19.924 --> 16:23.789
Some grinding stress of a long illness.

16:24.010 --> 16:25.672
I mean, tick your desperation.

16:26.553 --> 16:27.474
Life is hard.

16:29.090 --> 16:29.871
And God is good.

16:30.973 --> 16:32.315
We like to sing that, don't we?

16:35.821 --> 16:37.143
So that's the pit.

16:38.345 --> 16:40.769
We don't know what it was for David.

16:41.510 --> 16:49.443
And I'm glad we don't know, because I think that invites you in to say yours too.

16:53.009 --> 16:56.434
The king's pit, and then the king's cry, number two.

16:56.578 --> 16:59.401
Verse 1, I waited patiently for the Lord.

16:59.721 --> 17:03.505
He inclined to me and heard my cry.

17:03.906 --> 17:10.994
I think one of the reasons God calls David a man after his own heart while he has such an affection for David is because he cried so much.

17:11.935 --> 17:14.557
He cried out so much.

17:14.918 --> 17:18.201
Here's Psalm 6, I am weary with my mourning.

17:18.241 --> 17:22.546
Every night I flood my bed with tears.

17:23.202 --> 17:27.427
I drench my couch with my weeping."

17:29.569 --> 17:31.271
That's the man after God's own heart.

17:33.533 --> 17:37.057
Psalm 56, put my tears in your bottle.

17:38.258 --> 17:41.542
Are they not in your book?

17:41.562 --> 17:45.707
And of course, Jesus, blessed are those who mourn.

17:46.908 --> 17:52.594
It is a beautiful thing when a broken man

17:53.058 --> 17:55.060
genuinely cries out to God.

17:56.641 --> 18:10.755
It is not a beautiful thing when a macho jock tries to make his way to shore after getting a cramp hiding the fact that he's about to die and he's not going to let anybody know about it.

18:11.796 --> 18:12.676
That's not beautiful.

18:13.337 --> 18:14.338
He thinks it's beautiful.

18:14.478 --> 18:15.319
It's not beautiful.

18:15.759 --> 18:16.380
Not to God.

18:18.922 --> 18:22.265
I remember when I was in Daytona Beach on vacation with my parents.

18:22.406 --> 18:22.866
It's a little

18:22.946 --> 18:29.615
six-year-old or so, and you wait out just a little too far, and you know how the current works.

18:29.675 --> 18:38.967
It can just, and little kids just totally not ready for the power of the undertow sweeps me off my feet, and my first words are, Daddy?

18:39.007 --> 18:42.691
That's what God wants to hear.

18:43.713 --> 18:45.034
That's what God wants to hear.

18:45.054 --> 18:49.180
None of this fake, I don't need any help.

18:49.881 --> 18:50.962
That's ridiculous.

18:52.674 --> 18:58.961
You better own the need for help, women and men and little children and teenagers.

18:59.542 --> 19:01.504
We need help.

19:02.105 --> 19:07.471
And so he cries out and God is very pleased with the cry of his people.

19:10.534 --> 19:15.620
Blessed is the man, this is verse four, the next verse.

19:16.501 --> 19:20.786
Blessed is the man who has made the Lord his trust

19:21.378 --> 19:24.343
and who has not turned to the proud.

19:25.545 --> 19:29.872
In other words, when you cry out, be sure to cry out to God.

19:31.194 --> 19:37.224
That's a lot of people who are willing to recognize the need for help and they don't ask God.

19:37.244 --> 19:38.225
They ask other people.

19:39.587 --> 19:45.337
God, he's kind of maybe a last resort, not a first resort.

19:45.757 --> 19:46.719
That's backwards.

19:47.320 --> 19:48.722
That's his backwards.

19:49.346 --> 19:51.848
God should be our first resort.

19:51.888 --> 19:53.650
Do you remember Asa the king?

19:53.670 --> 20:02.779
Oh man, every time I read the stories of these kings and the old stuff, I just shake my head and say, oh my goodness, won't they ever learn?

20:02.799 --> 20:10.026
And of course, won't Piper ever learn to trust the Lord and not be anxious?

20:10.106 --> 20:18.674
But Asa relied upon Syria instead of the Lord and God spanked him for it.

20:18.850 --> 20:22.493
didn't kill him, just spanked him and disciplined him.

20:23.234 --> 20:25.596
And then you think, okay, he's got it.

20:26.457 --> 20:29.140
And at the end of his life, this is second chronicle, 1612.

20:29.860 --> 20:35.045
In the 39th year of his reign, Asa was diseased in his feet.

20:36.767 --> 20:38.689
And his disease became severe.

20:38.729 --> 20:48.498
And even in his disease, he did not seek the Lord, but he sought help from physicians.

20:50.050 --> 20:52.994
No, I thank God for physicians.

20:54.215 --> 20:56.037
This is not anti-physician.

20:56.418 --> 20:59.261
This is anti-making physicians or God.

21:01.604 --> 21:05.168
This is anti-defaulting to physicians.

21:05.709 --> 21:07.511
Oh yes, later God.

21:08.633 --> 21:10.194
That's what this text is against.

21:11.836 --> 21:16.402
When David was in the pit, he cried out to the Lord,

21:18.914 --> 21:29.050
And the Lord uses all kinds of means and medicine is a great gift of common grace that we should all be very, very thankful for.

21:29.090 --> 21:31.894
It is better to take refuge.

21:31.914 --> 21:33.016
This is Psalm 118.

21:33.376 --> 21:36.962
It is better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in man.

21:38.284 --> 21:42.911
It is better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in princes.

21:43.552 --> 21:47.538
So when you're in the pit, you cry out

21:48.162 --> 21:49.063
to God.

21:49.864 --> 21:57.994
Now he may use a therapist, a Christian counselor, may use a pastor, may use the Bible.

21:58.054 --> 22:05.202
He has a hundred ways to meet you and rescue you, but you call out to him.

22:05.242 --> 22:06.964
That's number two.

22:07.725 --> 22:15.154
The king's pit, the king's cry, and now thirdly, the king's patient waiting, the king's patience.

22:17.634 --> 22:22.939
Verse 1, I waited patiently for the Lord.

22:22.959 --> 22:35.631
The reason that's so important for us to hear is because waiting, I think Marshall's breakout yesterday was on waiting.

22:36.452 --> 22:41.557
Waiting is a huge portion of the Christian life.

22:43.279 --> 22:46.642
We could wish that answers came

22:47.170 --> 22:52.838
as soon as the request was made, and they don't come that way usually.

22:54.180 --> 22:56.202
God's timing is rarely your timing.

22:57.284 --> 23:00.909
I was a pastor for 33 years, and we were always desperate for something.

23:01.970 --> 23:02.992
Something wasn't working.

23:03.813 --> 23:06.577
Come to the end of the year, you need a third of your budget in December.

23:07.558 --> 23:10.442
Very typical, but oh my goodness.

23:10.482 --> 23:16.210
Four weeks left, need a million dollars, and God

23:16.866 --> 23:21.012
cancels your first service with a snowstorm like Gideon.

23:21.052 --> 23:23.275
You got too many Sundays to get a million dollars.

23:24.556 --> 23:25.818
Going to take one of them away.

23:25.858 --> 23:27.500
Nobody's showing up today.

23:29.243 --> 23:31.526
That's just the way it worked over and over again.

23:32.247 --> 23:33.128
And he came through.

23:33.148 --> 23:34.590
He came through.

23:35.171 --> 23:39.056
My God will supply all your needs according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus.

23:39.276 --> 23:40.518
If you don't get it, you don't need it.

23:42.480 --> 23:43.762
That's what I told the elders.

23:44.514 --> 23:45.776
If we don't get it, we don't need it.

23:45.796 --> 23:46.957
That's what it says in the Bible.

23:49.580 --> 23:51.663
He will supply every need.

23:54.807 --> 23:57.090
And our timing is seldom his.

23:58.411 --> 24:05.460
He knows the time for joy and truly will send it when he sees it meet.

24:06.721 --> 24:13.650
When he has tried and purged thee, do thee and finds thee free from all deceit.

24:14.050 --> 24:19.436
He comes to the all unaware and makes the on his loving care.

24:19.917 --> 24:20.658
I love that song.

24:21.238 --> 24:23.180
